article.headline: Jackson St. 74, Iona 70
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Sophomore forward Grant Maxey scored a career-high 23 points and along with a game-high nine rebounds to lead Jackson State over Iona 74-70 in the seventh-place game of the Las Vegas Invitational Saturday. Maxey from the field went 9-of-12, from the free-throw line 4-of-6, and two blocks. He also had 15 first-half points including 6-of-7 from the field. Also for Jackson State (1-5), Jeremy Caldwell had 16 points on 6-of-7 shooting from the field and 4-of-4 from the foul line. Darrion Griffin had 12 points and Chris Byche had 11. De?Shaune Griffin led Iona (0-6) with 14 points, while Milan Prodanovic had 11 points and five rebounds. Dexter Gray had 10 points and nine rebounds for the Gaels. The Tigers halftime lead of 34-29 was cut to 40-39 with 16:42 left, but Jackson State went on a 16-4 run. Iona made a late run, cutting the lead to 73-70 with 11 seconds left, but the Tigers held off the Gaels going 8-of-10 from the free-throw line in the final 1:09. For the game, the Tigers from the field shot 25-of-53 for 47 percent, while the Gaels were 23-of-51 for 51 percent. From the free-throw line, Jackson State went 21-of-37 for 57 percent, while Iona was 16-of-24 for 67 percent. Jackson State led for just about all of the first half, building two seven-point leads, the last at 31-24 with 3:10 left in the half.
